the duke takes the burden of aerial command in wwii john wayne stars in this thoroughly entertaining film about marine wwii pilots . the duke takes command and drives his men hard to accomplish the mission of close air support - a very dangerous endeavor . while his xo does not agree with his methods , he does come to appreciate them later on . flying leathernecks includes some excellent real combat footage from wwii , which adds a nice touch of authenticity . the characters and dialogue will engage the viewer , and really help keep the plot moving along . if you like the movie flying tigers , or other wwii aviation films then you will enjoy this one . or , if you simply like the duke in military films , then this one is also worth viewing .